# 🏓 Pong Game

A simple implementation of the classic **Pong game** built with Python.  
This project recreates the retro arcade experience where two players control paddles to keep the ball in play.

---

## 📂 Project Structure
- `main.py` – Main game loop and logic  
- `paddle.py` – Paddle class and movement  
- `score.py` – Scoreboard display and tracking  
- `setup.py` – Setup file for packaging  
- `*.pyc` – Compiled Python files (auto-generated)

---

## ✨ Features
- Two-player gameplay  
- Real-time paddle movement  
- Score tracking  
- Ball bouncing mechanics  
- Restart option when game ends  

---

## 🛠 Requirements
Make sure you have the following installed:
- Python 3.x  

You may also need the **Turtle graphics** library (comes built-in with Python).  

